BEGIN_PGML
Demonstrate that you know the meanings of the various algebraic properties by applying the given algebraic property to the given expression to get a new expression.

Apply the distributive property to [`[$given]\text{.}`]

[_]{$evaluator}{16}

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
The expression has a group of two terms multiplied by [`[$a]\text{.}`] To apply the distributive property, we multiply [`[$a]`] by each of those two terms. This gives us [`[$ans]\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

